      "symbol": "CacheDelegator"
    },
    {
      "repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes",
      "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/store.go",
      "symbol": "store"
    },
    {
      "repo": "grafana/grafana",
      "path": "pkg/storage/unified/apistore/store.go",
      "symbol": "Storage"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage.Interface is explicitly implemented across two different GitHub organizations using the Go compile-time interface compliance check pattern `var _ storage.Interface = (*StructName)(nil)`. In kubernetes/kubernetes (owned by the kubernetes organization), the interface is implemented by two structs: CacheDelegator in the cacher layer (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/delegator.go line 89) which provides a delegating wrapper around the underlying storage interface, and store in the etcd3 storage backend (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/store.go line 100) which is the actual etcd-backed storage implementation. In grafana/grafana (owned by the grafana organization), the interface is implemented by the Storage struct (pkg/storage/unified/apistore/store.go line 52) which provides a unified storage abstraction for Grafana's resource API layer. These implementations demonstrate that both the Kubernetes project and the Grafana project, from different organizations, have independently implemented the same storage abstraction interface, confirming platform compatibility and cross-organization adoption of the Kubernetes storage backend pattern."
}

